## Casing by Kind
- Classes/Scenes & Node names: **PascalCase** (`EnemySpawner`, `HealthBar.gd`, `PlayerShip.tscn`).
- Files: **snake_case** (`enemy_spawner.gd`, `boss_room.tscn`).
- Variables & functions: **snake_case** (`current_hp`, `apply_damage()`).
- Constants: **SCREAMING_SNAKE** (`MAX_ENEMIES`).

## Booleans
- Must start with **is_** or **has_** (`is_alive`, `has_keycard`).

## Units in Names (make physics explicit)
- Suffixes: **_px, _tiles, _s, _ms, _deg, _rad, _px_s**.
- Examples: `move_speed_px_s`, `cooldown_s`, `rotation_deg`.

## Signals & Handlers
- Signals: **past-tense snake_case** (`enemy_spawned`, `player_damaged`, `room_cleared`).
- Handlers: **on_<source>_<signal>()** (`on_spawner_enemy_spawned()`).

## Privacy & API Surface
- Leading `_` means **private**; public API has no underscore.

## Exports & Singletons
- `@export var` names **must include units** where relevant.
- Autoload singletons are **PascalCase** (`Events`, `GameConfig`, `SaveBus`) and used sparingly.

## Function Verbs = Intent
- Accessors: `get_/set_` for pure access.
- Side-effects: `apply_/spawn_/schedule_/ensure_/try_` (don’t invent synonyms).

## Abbreviation Whitelist (the only allowed)
- **id, ui, hp, xp, ai, fx, rng, pos, vel**. Everything else: **spell it out**.
